AlfredCircle - Privacy Policy
Effective Date: July 28 , 2023
AlfredCircle (also referred to as “we,” “us” or “our”) treats your data seriously and is committed to putting every effort in to ensure your privacy is safe and secure. This privacy policy (this “Policy”) describes how and why we collect, store, use, share and protect the information obtained from the individuals who register to use AlfredCircle as a user. This Policy also describes the action you can take when you have concerns about our privacy practices.
We pledge to collect and process your information under these principles:
We will be as transparent as possible, including how we use your information and whom we share it with.
We will keep your information as secure and safe as possible by implementing security measures in line with industry standards.
We will ask for your consent when there is new personal data to be collected/shared.
By using AlfredCircle, you agree to allow us to collect and process the information about you for the purposes described below. Under no circumstances do our products and services access your information without receiving your consent first.
How Is The Information Collected and Used
We obtain certain personal information about you and information that is related to your experience with our products and services. The below table will help you know more about what information we collect, and how we use it:
A. Account Information
Type
Source
Purpose
Name
User provide in registration process
Account name that relates to an identifiable account.
Email address
User provide in registration process
Email address that relates to an identifiable account.
User ID
System generated in the registration process
User ID that relates to a registered account.
Language
From device API
Determine the display language
B. Location
Type
Source
Purpose
Registered location
Derive location information from an IP address
1. Determine default service provider (API and storage server).
2. Used to improve service quality and resolve issues.
Last login location
Derive location information from an IP address
1. Determine the default service provider (API and storage server).
2. Used to improve service quality and resolve issues.
Real-time Precise Location and Coarse Location
Derive location information from an IP address
1. Display the real-time location of specific individuals on a map. This feature allows group members to stay connected with their designated contacts and provides them with the ability to view and track the whereabouts of their family members.
2. AlfredCircle is also using location services in the background to provide a key safety feature: so family members can receive real-time geofence alerts from other members of the group.
C. Circle Information
Type
Source
Purpose
Circle Member Names
Users provide during the Circle joining process
1. Enables the Circle owner to manage the members within the Circle, enabling features such as communication and location sharing.
2. The display of member names aids in identifying and distinguishing individual members, facilitating effective communication and coordination within the Circle.
Place Info
The user adds a place under the Circle during the place addition process.
1. Enables the Circle owner to manage the places within the Circle.
2. Enables the Circle owner to monitor the entry and exit of Circle members from specific locations.
3. Customize your in-app map by labeling places of interest, such as “work” and “home,” for easy identification and to receive alerts when Circle members or a Tile device leave or arrive, using the “Smart Alert” feature.
D. Fitness
