Statutory Notice on Use of Personal Data (for Taiwan)
(a) Name of the Entity Collecting Personal Data: Alfred Systems Inc.
(b) Purposes of Collection: Matters relating to products and services provided by AlfredCircle such as “Contracts, Quasi-contracts or other Legal Matters,” “Consumer/ Customer Management and Service,” “Information (Communication) Service,” “Information (Communication) and Database Management,” “Security and Management,” “Advertising or Commercial Activity Management,” “Commercial and Technical Information,” “Other Advisory and Consulting Service,” “Other Businesses Conforming to the Business Registration Items or the Articles of Association.”
© Categories of Personal Data: Identification Category: (C001) identification of individuals, (C003) identification of governmental data, etc.; Characteristic Categories: (C011) personal description, (C012) physical description, etc.; Family Situation: (C021) family situation, (C022) marriage history, (C023) details of other family members, (C024) other social relations; Social Situation: (C031) home and facilities, (C032) property, (C033) immigration circumstances, (C034) travel and other details of relocation, (C035) leisure activities and interests, etc; Education, Examination, Technology, or other Profession Category: (C056) works, etc.
(d) Areas where the Personal Data is Used: Where Alfred Systems Inc. operates its businesses and the server locates.
(e) The Method Personal Data is Used: The Personal Data is used in accordance with this Policy and the Terms of Service.
(f) Third Parties using Personal Data: Alfred Systems Inc., Alfred Systems Inc.’s affiliates, and the business partners Alfred Systems Inc. has worked with (e.g., service providers that provide logistics and cash flow services, and designated verification service organizations); if Alfred Systems Inc. and other third party will jointly collect personal data, it will be stated in the joint collection statement.
(g) The Method Exercising Personal Data Rights: According to Article 3 of the Taiwan Personal Data Protection Law, you have the right to inquiry, the right to request copies of your collected personal data, the right to correct your personal data, the right to stop personal data collection, processing or utilizing, and the right to delete your personal data. You can send an e-mail to our customer service email:
support@alfredcircle.com
(in order to avoid any missing email or failure to receive the email for any other reasons, it is subject to our acknowledgement of receipt).
(h) If you choose not to provide necessary personal data required by Alfred Systems Inc. to provide our products or services, you will not be able to fully experience our products or services, or Alfred Systems Inc. will not be able to provide you with our products or services.
